description:
&lt;p&gt;We are delighted to offer this fixed term vacancy to join the collaborative care group as a Trauma Nurse practitioner, for immediate commencement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is full time position working on the Orthopaedic wards at University Hospital of North Tees. This is a busy unit and you will be required to work autonomously, supporting the multi professional team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of orthopaedic / trauma conditions is essential, but additional training will be provided. The role requires the post holder to work in a extended role supplementing the junior Dr role within the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential that you can evidence recent study at level 6.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The a physical examination skills qualification and a non-medical prescribing qualification would be desirable , however training would be available to support the suitable candidate, along with relevant ward based competencies’.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On achievement of these qualifications and competencies the post will be graded as a band 7.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The directorate prides itself on high standards of care with excellent learning opportunities. We also have an ortho geriatric shared approach for the management of fragility fractures and therefore a great opportunity for the right individual to gain further experience in this area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
